Performance Testing and Optimization
Description

The Performance Testing and Optimization phase focuses on evaluating the system’s efficiency, speed, and stability under different workloads. The goal is to ensure that the Voice-Based Communication Evaluation System performs smoothly during transcription, embedding generation, and audio feature extraction, even for longer audio inputs and repeated evaluations.

1. Runtime Performance Measurement

The system performance was measured for the following components:

a) Speech-to-Text Transcription
Time taken to convert audio into text was recorded.
Performance tested on short, medium, and long audio files.
b) Embedding Computation
Sentence embeddings were generated using transformer models.
Computation time was measured for semantic similarity tasks.
c) Audio Feature Extraction
Features such as duration, speaking rate, and pauses were extracted.
Execution time was tracked for each process.
Result
The system showed efficient processing for short and medium audio inputs.
Slight increase in runtime observed for longer audio files, but within acceptable limits.
2. Optimization Techniques

To improve performance and reduce latency, the following optimizations were implemented:

a) Streamlit Caching
Used @st.cache_resource for model loading.
Prevented repeated loading of heavy models like Whisper and Sentence Transformers.
import streamlit as st
from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer

@st.cache_resource
def load_model():
    model = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')
    return model
b) Efficient Model Loading
Models are loaded only once at startup.
Avoided re-initialization during each evaluation.
c) Reduced Redundant Computations
Stored intermediate results such as embeddings.
Prevented repeated processing of the same audio input.
3. Stability Testing

The system was tested under repeated and heavy usage scenarios.

Test Cases
Scenario	Result
Multiple evaluations (10+ runs)	Stable performance
Long audio input (5–10 minutes)	No crashes
Rapid repeated uploads	No memory leaks
Continuous transcription requests	Consistent output
4. Performance Summary
Component	Performance
Transcription	Fast for short audio, moderate for long audio
Embedding Generation	Optimized using caching
Feature Extraction	Efficient and stable
Overall System	Stable under repeated use
5. Conclusion

The performance testing confirmed that the system is efficient, stable, and optimized for real-world usage. By implementing Streamlit caching and optimizing model loading, the system significantly reduced latency and improved responsiveness. The application remains stable even under repeated evaluations and longer audio inputs.